WYSIWYM.ontology
Class QueryResult

java.lang.Object
  WYSIWYM.ontology.QueryResult

public class QueryResult
extends Object

QueryResult stores the bindings of a SPARQL query in a better sorted way than the BindingSets that Sesame returns. This is simply a helper method to make sense of Sesame's RDF retrieval. A QueryResult can be created from a TupleQueryResult by passing the query's variables to the constructor, and adding the binding sets one-by-one using add(BindingSet). Results are stored by their Sesame ID. Either your SPARQL query should request the Sesame ID as the first variable, or you should specify each BindingSet's Sesame ID yourself using add(BindingSet, String id).

Version:
1.2 12-03-2008, 1.3 22-03-2008
Author:
Feikje Hielkema

getNoLayout

public Map<String,String> getNoLayout(String head)
Returns a HashMap with descriptions of each search result, without html-tags. The description does include occurences of 'LINEBREAK' which signal where a linebreak should be inserted. This method is used by ourSpaces. 'head' determines which variable should be presented first (e.g. 'name').

Parameters:
head - First variable
Returns:
Map with a description for each search result.

getNLValue

public String getNLValue(String id,
                         List<String> nlproperties)
Returns the NL-information about the given Sesame ID. The second parameter is a list of properties that hold NL-information. This method is used by LIBER to quickly extract relevant information about objects. It could be used with any list of properties, not just for NL-information!

Parameters:
id - Sesame ID
nlproperties - List of property names that will be included in the description if they are in the BindingSet.
